snippet: Tiger Woods, who has not won a major tournament for six years and is coming off back surgery, said that an acceptable finish at this week’s British Open would be first place.
abstract: Time is running out for Tiger Woods's pursuit of Jack Nicklaus's record of 18 major championships; 38-year-old Woods will resume quest for 15th major title at Royal Liverpool after missing year's first two majors due to spine surgery.
lead_paragraph: Tiger Woods, who has not won a major tournament for six years and is coming off back surgery, said that an acceptable finish at this week’s British Open would be first place.

headline.seo: British Open 2014: Tiger Woods Resumes Chase for 15th Major Title
headline.main: It’s Woods and It’s Royal Liverpool, but It’s Not 2006
headline.print_headline: Stronger Body but Shrinking Window for Woods
